  "12:24:45",assistant,text,"Ah — now I see the real design fork, and you've put your finger on exactly the tension I was dancing around. You're right: chopping the voice into 50-char pieces to fit the bubble **wrecks the natural flow** — that clause should be *one breath*.\n\nSo here's the honest pivot, and it reverses my earlier revert:\n\n**Your requirement — \"long clause in single voice\" — means the voice can't be chopped to fit the bubble.** So voice = whole sentence (natural flow), and the *caption* has to **page through** a long sentence while the voice plays unbroken. That's renderer-side display-paging — the thing I built, then reverted. **But I reverted it for the wrong reason** — a word-by-word *bug* (bad height measurement), not because paging is wrong. Paging is actually *required* for what you want. So I'm bringing it back, rewritten robustly, and putting the voice back to whole sentences.\n\nOne honest tradeoff: with voice = one unbroken clip, the caption follows it **approximately** (syllable-timed), because Kokoro doesn't hand us exact per-word timings. Natural voice, roughly-synced caption. That's the trade for the flow you want.\n\nBuilding it. First, voice back to whole sentences (server):"
