  "12:29:37",assistant,spoke,"Here is how it is possible, and it is kind of beautiful. I stopped trying to chop my voice to fit the bubble. The voice stays one whole clip, Kokoro speaks the sentence naturally, commas and all. And the caption just watches the audio's own progress bar. Every audio player knows how far through it is, so I split the text into pages that fit the bubble, weight each page by its syllables, and flip to the next page when the sound crosses that page's share of the timeline. The voice never even knows the caption exists. The caption just rides its clock. No word timing needed, just proportion."
  "12:29:50",assistant,text,"Committed — `198843a`, the two code files, clean.\n\n**How it's possible — the trick is *decoupling*:**\n\nThe mistake I kept making was trying to chop the *voice* to fit the *bubble*. Once I stopped doing that, it fell out easily. Three pieces:\n\n1. **The voice is one clip.** Kokoro speaks the whole sentence — commas, rhythm, all of it — as a single unbroken utterance. Natural by construction, because I'm not touching it.\n2. **The caption rides the audio's own clock.** Every browser `<audio>` element knows `currentTime / duration` — its own progress bar. So I split the text into pages, weight each page by its **syllable count** (speech-time tracks syllables, not characters), and flip to the next page the instant playback crosses that page's share of the timeline. The voice doesn't know the caption exists; the caption just *watches* the voice and turns the page. No per-word timing from Kokoro needed — just proportion.\n3. **The pages actually fit** because I size them by *measuring* the real rendered height against a 4-line budget (with the clamp toggled off so the measurement is honest) — and that exact measurement fix is what killed the word-by-word bug from before.\n\nSo: natural voice + a caption that follows it + pages that always fit, all from one idea — *let the caption follow the voice's clock instead of forcing the voice to match the caption.*\n\nThat's the whole avatar-bubble thread done and committed. `self-forming` is 5 ahead of origin now. What's next, K — back to the qualia we never started? 🔥"
