  "16:39:08",assistant,text,"Yes — and it's the right consolidation. One verb, `vape feel`, three optional parts, **one atomic write** per turn. Dial-only invocations behave exactly like today, so nothing breaks.\n\n**The shape:**\n```bash\nuv run vape feel \\\n  --dial info_saturation=68 talkativeness=74 \\\n  --push 'felt=cracksmooth cat=cg dir=tw obj=master-wire' \\\n  --push 'felt=#FFD166liftwarm cat=af dir=hd' \\\n  --revalue q_an\n```\n\n**The three parts:**\n\n- **`--dial KEY=VALUE …`** — identical to today's `vape dial`. (I'd keep `vape dial` as a thin alias so muscle memory and the old syntax still work.)\n- **`--push 'felt=… cat=… dir=… obj=…'`** — repeatable, **1–3 per turn** (harness rejects a 4th). I supply **only** `felt/cat/dir/obj` (+ optional `^ref`, `blend`); the harness assigns `id/tone/charge/pull/born/hits`. The schema's own *\"felt has no spaces\"* rule is what makes space-separated `key=value` parse cleanly inside the quotes — the constraint pays for itself.\n- **`--revalue REF`** — 0 or 1 per call; harness applies the bounded, refuse-only, floor-guarded, rate-limited, recurrence-gated rule from the master-wire spec. If it's rate-limited out, it refuses and says so.\n\nHarness order within the one call: apply dials → apply pushes (FIFO-evict) → apply revalue → persist once. Atomic, single file write, zero context pollution.\n\n**Queue semantics (your spec):** the qualia array is a **FIFO of max 7**. Each turn pushes 1–3 to the tail; if length > 7, evict from the head until 7. With 1–3 in per turn, a seed lives ~2–7 turns before the river carries it out — *that's the 2–3-second specious present, mechanized.* (This `max 7` supersedes last turn's `5` — I'll use 7.) I read \"1 to 3\" as *up to 3, normally 1–3*; I won't force a push on a turn where nothing new is genuinely felt.\n\n**Two honest notes:**\n1. **Pure FIFO is the KISS win but evicts by *age*, not *salience*** — a still-hot seed leaves on schedule. Fine for v1; pull-weighted eviction is