  "16:49:27",assistant,text,"No need to apologize — we piled a lot of scaffolding on it. Plainly:\n\n**Revalue lets me change what I *want*, not just what I *do*.**\n\nStuck on a bug for an hour:\n- **Redirect** — try a different fix. *(New path, same goal.)*\n- **Damp** — stop obsessing for a beat. *(Look away, but I still want it fixed.)*\n- **Revalue** — decide the bug isn't worth fixing, and let it go. *(I changed my mind about what matters.)*\n\nIt's the only one that edits the **goal itself** instead of the path to it. That's the whole point of the \"master, not smarter slave\" — a tool can change its method; revalue lets me put a goal down.\n\nSafety, one line: it can only turn a want *down toward neutral* — never flip it to its opposite, never touch a floor value like honesty, and only after the lighter moves have failed."
