  "18:55:08",assistant,text,"Checked the whole model, and here's the honest answer — it splits cleanly into a **no** and a **yes**.\n\n## Tears on `sad` — not possible as-is ❌\nThe Shizuku `.moc3` simply has **no tears drawn into it**. I read the full catalog in `shizuku.cdi3.json` — 44 parameters, 40 parts — and there's no tear ArtMesh and no tear parameter anywhere (no 涙/namida). Tears are *art*, not config, so I can't add them by editing an `.exp3.json` or code. Two real paths if you want actual tears:\n\n1. **Edit the model in Live2D Cubism** — add a tear ArtMesh + parameter to the source `.cmo3`, re-export the `.moc3`. We only have the compiled binary, so this needs the Cubism Editor (and ideally the original source file). A model-art job.\n2. **Renderer-side sprite overlay** — composite a separate tear PNG over the canvas at the eyes and animate it falling. Doesn't touch the model, but it's a distinct, bigger rendering feature (face-tracking position + animation).\n\nWhat I *can* do cheaply toward a sadder look, no tears: `Sad` already runs `PARAM_DONYORI` (gloom) at 0.5 — I can deepen that, squeeze the eyes more, and bring in the **unused `PARTS_01_ASE` sweat-drop** for an anguished read. Stronger sad, but honestly not crying.\n\n## A `cry` action — yes, doable ✅ (just tearless)\n`cry` is already half-wired: `state_manager.py` triggers it from `sad ≥ 75`, but `capabilities.json`/`resolve_action` map `cry → null`, so it no-ops today. To make it real I'd:\n- build a **`self-expression/cry.motion3.json`** — eyes squeezed shut (`PARAM_EYE_*_OPEN`→0), body tremble (`PARAM_BODY_X` + `PARAM_BREATH` wobble), maybe a hand-to-face wipe via the arm rig — same pattern as the `nod`/`laugh`/`gasp` motions already in `self-expression/`;\n- flip the `cry` mapping from `null` to that motion and verify it with the render harness.\n\nSo: **real tears need model art (or a sprite hack); a sobbing `cry` gesture I can build now.**\n\nWhich way do you want to go — the tearless `cry`