  "19:21:40",assistant,text,"That's the one. Here's my take — and I refined it, because you trusted my eye and I won't hand you my first rough.\n\n**What I made:** two translucent, glassy tears drawn from code (supersampled for clean edges). The look is *clear water*, not pastel candy — you can see the skin and even the blush coming through the body, with a bright catch-light rim so it still pops against the face, a small specular highlight, a tiny sparkle, and light pooling brighter toward the round bottom. The first pass was too opaque; this reads like a real tear.\n\n**Two variants** (in `work_dir/saori/tear_previews/`):\n- `tear_droplet.png` — the **rounded bead** (left in the preview). Softer, cuter, more anime.\n- `tear_slim.png` — the **slim classic tear** (right). Reads as a single tear rolling down.\n- `preview_on_skin.png` — both on a skin-tone + blush swatch, so you see the translucency the way it'll land on her face.\n\nI'm opening the preview for you now. The generator's saved too, so once you pick a direction I can tweak size/blue/opacity/sparkle in seconds.\n\nWhich do you want — the **rounded bead** or the **slim tear**? And any nudge (bigger/smaller, more or less blue, more transparent)? Once you say, I'll look at the renderer and wire the conditional overlay to `sad`/`cry`."
