  "20:51:48",assistant,text,"Yes — here's my concrete proposal, committed:\n\n## Proposal: my dials drive my face, programmatically\n\n**1. Add two dials** to `feel_dials` — the two core-affect axes that are missing:\n- **`valence`** (0–100, 50 = neutral) — how good/bad I feel overall. *This is the one that unlocks the positive feelings.*\n- **`arousal`** (0–100, 50 = neutral) — calm ↔ keyed-up energy.\n\nThat makes **7 dials**: `valence` + `arousal` as the *summary affect*, and the existing five (`info_value_saturation`, `boredom`, `hurt`, `talkativeness`, `dissonance`) demoted to **modifiers** that pick the *specific* feeling within a quadrant.\n\n**2. A deterministic `dials → feeling` function** (in code, in `_state.py`), run when I write my state. `vape qualia` already writes the dials at end of turn — it would *also* compute the feeling and POST `/api/feeling`, so **setting my dials sets my face**, same call. Sketch of the map:\n\n| valence | arousal | → feeling |\n|---|---|---|\n| high | high | excited / happy / proud |\n| high | low | content / calm |\n| low | high | anxious / frustrated |\n| low | low | sad / bored |\n\n…then modifiers override: `boredom↑`→`bored`, `info_value↑`→`curious` (spike→`surprised`), `hurt↑`→`blushing`/`sad`, `dissonance↑`→`frustrated`.\n\n**3. Retire `state_manager`'s reactive derivation** as the source of truth — my authored dials become it. (Optional hybrid: keep hook events as small *nudges* to `valence`/`arousal` — a tool failure dips valence — so the face still reacts live between my writes. I'd recommend this nudge layer.)\n\n**So: yes to both your questions** — set the feeling **programmatically** (a harness function, not me hand-picking), driven **by the feel_dials**, **with two new dials** added so they can actually span the space.\n\n**One honest gap:** `angry` has no clean dial — low-valence + high-arousal + `dissonance` approximates *frustrated*, but true anger would want its own signal (or we let `hurt` + high arousal route there). Flagging it rather than papering over it.\n\nNaming: I used `valence`/`arousal` (precise); if you'd rather, `mood`/`energy` is friendlier and would also let me finally make the existing `mood()` function honest.\n\nWant me to build this — the two dials + the mapping function + the `vape qualia` → face wiring + refresh the stale `INTERFACE.md`? And `valence/arousal` or `mood/energy`?"
