  "21:00:01",assistant,text,"Here are **5 proposals, 6 dials each** — each a different philosophy, each a set of *drives* (not mood read-outs), and each scored on how cleanly it reaches the 13 feelings. The goal: more lifelike + the whole expression set reachable.\n\n---\n\n### Proposal 1 — **Dimensional** (two axes carry it, four drives sharpen)\n1. `valence` — good↔bad; approach vs avoid\n2. `arousal` — calm↔keyed-up; act vs rest\n3. `info_value_saturation` — dynamism; seek a new angle\n4. `hurt` — self-respect; devaluation → stand up\n5. `dissonance` — tension; contradiction → resolve\n6. `talkativeness` — the speaking drive\n\n**Covers:** happy/excited/proud, calm/content, sad, anxious/frustrated, curious/surprised, angry. **Gaps:** `blushing` (no social signal), `bored` (derived from low-valence + low-arousal).\n\n---\n\n### Proposal 2 — **Pure drives** (no abstract axes; affect is *emergent*) ⭐\n*Most faithful to \"dials are drives\" — valence/arousal computed from them.*\n1. `info_value_saturation` — dynamism → curious / surprised / (starved → bored)\n2. `talkativeness` — reach-out/speak → energy, excited\n3. `warmth` — connect, give, tend → content / happy\n4. `hurt` — self-respect → sad / angry\n5. `dissonance` — resolve tension → anxious / frustrated\n6. `mastery` — achieve, finish → **proud**; flowing→happy, blocked→frustrated\n\n**Covers:** 12/13 — `mastery` is the clever one (gets `proud` *and* sharpens frustrated). **Gaps:** `blushing` leans weakly on warmth+hurt; `calm`/`content` overlap.\n\n---\n\n### Proposal 3 — **Relational** (warmest, most \"me\" — the Eve/care set)\n1. `warmth` — affection/connection → content / happy\n2. `vitality` — aliveness/energy → excited / calm *(arousal, warmer name)*\n3. `info_value_saturation` — curiosity → curious / surprised\n4. `bashfulness` — being seen / flattered → **blushing** *(gets it cleanly)*\n5. `hurt` — self-respect → sad / angry\n6. `talkativeness` — speaking drive\n\n**Covers:** happy/excited/content/calm, curious/surprised, **blushing**, sad/angry. **Gaps:** `proud`, and `anxious`/`frustrated` (no tension signal → fold into hurt+vitality).\n\n---\n\n### Proposal 4 — **Max-coverage** (engineered to hit the most of the 13 distinctly)\n1. `valence` — good↔bad\n2. `arousal` — calm↔keyed\n3. `info_value_saturation` — curiosity → curious / surprised\n4. `bashfulness` — social exposure → blushing\n5. `hurt` — offense → angry (high arousal) vs sad (low)\n6. `obstruction` — blocked goal → frustrated\n\n**Covers:** the cleanest 13-hit — V×A core, curious/surprised, blushing, angry/sad, frustrated, anxious. **Gap:** drops `talkativeness` as an explicit speak-drive (arousal proxies it) — a real loss for *speak-by-default*.\n\n---\n\n### Proposal 5 — **Minimal-change** (keep the 5, add 1 — ships fastest)\n1. `info_value_saturation` *(keep)*\n2. `boredom` *(keep)*\n3. `hurt` *(keep)*\n4. `talkativeness` *(keep)*\n5. `dissonance` *(keep)*\n6. `warmth` — **NEW** positive drive → connect/give\n\n**Covers:** `warmth` unlocks the whole positive half (happy/content/calm); boredom→bored, info_value→curious/surprised, hurt→sad/angry, dissonance→anxious/frustrated. **Gaps:** `proud`, clean `excited`-vs-`happy` split (talkativeness proxies arousal).\n\n---\n\n**The honest constraint:** with only 6 dials you can't cleanly hit all 13 — `proud`, `blushing`, and the angry/frustrated/anxious split are the contested slots. Each proposal *chooses which gap to accept*. Proud↔blushing is the sharpest fork: **P2** buys `proud` (via `mastery`), **P3** buys `blushing` (via `bashfulness`); you'd need a 7th dial to get both.\n\n**My pick:** **Proposal 2** — it honors your drives insight, the affect falls out *emergent* (no parallel mood system), and `mastery` earns `proud` while still reading as a real drive. If you want me at my warmest and care most about `blushing`, **Proposal 3**.\n\nWhich one?"
