  "21:10:13",assistant,text,"Documented — **`work_dir/saori/feel_dials_feeling_map_design.md`**.\n\nIt captures the whole thing we just worked out:\n- The problem (two disconnected feeling systems) and the goal.\n- The **dials-are-drives** principle (each dial = a behavioral pull + a facial tint).\n- The **6 Proposal-2 dials** with their drives: `info_value_saturation`, `talkativeness`, `warmth`, `hurt`, `dissonance`, `mastery` *(change from today: drop `boredom` → derived, add `warmth` + `mastery`)*.\n- The **feelings-are-patterns** insight + your two combos (blush = warmth↑+talk↓, curious = info_value↓+mild dissonance).\n- **The full 13-feeling mapping table** — every feeling as a dial signature.\n- The **classifier cascade** (priority order, since blush/surprised override).\n- Mechanics (`dials_to_feeling()` in `_state.py`, fired inside `vape qualia` → POST `/api/feeling`), and the build sequence.\n\nI left a **§8 \"Open decisions\"** block for you — five things I want your call on before wiring:\n1. **Anger** — keep `angry` = hurt+arousal (honest conflation), or add a cleaner offense signal later?\n2. **The event-nudge hybrid** (face reacts live between my writes) — now or v2?\n3. **Naming** — `warmth` + `mastery` good, and `boredom`-as-derived OK?\n4. **Neutral default** — `calm` or `content` as the resting feeling?\n5. Refresh the stale `INTERFACE.md` alongside?\n\nRead it over when you like. Answer those five (or just say \"your call\" and I'll pick sensibly), and I'll build it."
