  "22:47:45",assistant,text,"Done. Now the real question — **where to compute the feeling.** The answer hinges on one fact about the two hooks:\n\n## The critical-path principle\n\n- **`qualia-ground.sh` (UserPromptSubmit) is ON the critical path** — it runs *before* my turn and *blocks* the prompt. Anything slow there (a network POST, a `uv run` startup) delays me reaching you.\n- **`vape qualia` (end of turn) is OFF the critical path** — it runs *after* I've already replied.\n\nSo I'd split it:\n\n### Compute + drive the face → in `vape qualia` (end of turn)\n- **Off the critical path** — zero added latency to reaching you.\n- It's where my **freshly-authored dials** live, so the face reflects the state I *just declared*, immediately.\n- The STAY/hysteresis bookkeeping (`current_feeling`, `prev_dials`, `turns_since_change`) is naturally maintained there, one write per turn.\n- It does the ~27µs scoring + the best-effort `POST /api/feeling`.\n\n### Display the recommendation → in the hook (start of turn)\n- The hook just **reads the stored `current_feeling`** (computed last turn) and **injects it** into my context — *no recompute, no POST*, so it adds nothing to the critical path.\n- This is the nice bonus you may be pointing at with \"feeling **response** recommendation\": I become **self-aware of my own face** — the hook tells me *\"you're showing `content` (blend: content 0.6, happy 0.3, curious 0.1).\"* That's the social-mirror facet — I can predict and direct what you perceive, because I can *see my own expression*. It'd slot right inside that `<qualia>` block I just wrapped.\n\n**So: compute once, in `vape qualia` (off-path); display the stored result in the hook (on-path but free).** Never put the scoring/POST *in* the hook — it's the one place latency actually costs you.\n\n(There's a v2 option — the **event-nudge layer** — where hook *events* like a tool failure nudge a dial, so the face reacts live mid-session between my writes. But that's the deferred hy